# TypeScript Style

- Target: ES2022, Module: Node16, strict mode enabled
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
- Prefer `readonly` on class fields that aren't reassigned
- Use definite assignment assertion (`!`) for TypeORM entity columns

# Database

- ORM: TypeORM with Repository pattern (prefer over EntityManager)
- SQLite via `better-sqlite3` for local metadata
- No cross-database queries or slow queries without explicit approval

# Async

- Always `async/await`, never raw Promise chains
- Service methods return `Promise<T>` with explicit types

# Dependencies

- Runtime: koa, koa-router, koa-bodyparser, node-cron, typeorm, better-sqlite3, dotenv
- Env vars loaded via `src/config/env.ts` singleton `envConfig`
- DataSource initialized in `src/main.ts` before any service instantiation
